COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; USC; FRESHMEN COULD PLAY KEY ROLE SATURDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Baylor puts much emphasis on the fact it has a 3-0 record with three freshman 
starters and seven freshman backups. However, USC is playing two freshman 
starters and eight freshman backups. . . . Baylor defensive coordinator Bob 
Cope was USC's secondary coach in 1991 and '92, and Baylor strength and 
conditioning Coach Robb Rogers held the same position at USC from 1989-92. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The 68-yard interception return by Quincy Harrison at Penn State was the 
longest by a Trojan since Cleveland Colter went 94 yards on a 1987 return at 
California. . . . Punter John Stonehouse is off to a fast start. The junior 
from Pasadena is the early Pac-10 leader at 43.3 yards per punt, which puts him 
16th in the country. . . . USC has 38 active NFL players, more than any other 
school. Next are Notre Dame (34), UCLA (29), Tennessee (27), Ohio State and 
Washington (24). EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
