<TEXT>
<P>
 Costa Mesa running back Charles Chatman rushed for a game-high 211 yards and 
two touchdowns in a 28-16 victory over Lakewood Mayfair in a nonleague game 
Thursday night at Bellflower High. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatman has rushed for 552 yards this season.Costa Mesa is 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Ball control was the game plan for the Mustangs, who ran 36 plays to Mayfair's 
14 in the first half, rushing for 173 yards to the Monsoons' 59 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 After a scoreless first quarter, Costa Mesa took advantage of a two-yard punt 
by Mayfair from its 27-yard line. Five plays later, Chatman dived over from the 
one-yard line for a 6-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 After another short punt, this one by Costa Mesa, Mayfair took possession on 
the Mustang 47-yard line. Four plays later, Brady Green caught a 39-yard 
touchdown pass from Shawn Augustine on his fingertips and Mayfair took a 7-6 
lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatman scored again from three yards to put the Mustangs ahead, 14-7, at 
halftime. RICK CHRISTOPHER 
