<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP CROSS-COUNTRY; SANCHEZ AND GARRITSON HIGHLIGHT MEETS THIS WEEKEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT FARMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Runners from more than 70 high schools will compete Saturday at the Dana Hills 
Invitational cross-country meet, which begins at 8 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The competition will have three divisions based on school enrollment, and the 
races will be by grade level except the three combination junior-senior girls' 
races. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine, the county's top-ranked girls' team, meets No. 3 El Toro, which 
produced the fastest team time at Saturday's Woodbridge Invitational, in a 
junior-senior Division I race at 9:15 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 The boys' senior Division I race, beginning at 9:30, features Capistrano 
Valley's Adalberto Sanchez, who finished third at last year's Orange County 
Championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Three ranked teams -- No. 2 Newport Harbor, No. 5 Villa Park and No. 8 Laguna 
Hills -- will compete in the senior Division II boys' race. The girls' 
junior-senior Division II race will feature No. 9 Los Alamitos, Laguna Hills, 
Canyon and Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 Division III competition, which begins at noon, is highlighted by San Diego 
Scripps Ranch, Corona del Mar and Trabuco Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 In North Orange County on Saturday, more than 1,000 runners from 50 high 
schools will take part in the 17th Sonora Invitational, which begins at 7:20 
a.m. at Carbon Canyon Regional Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Among those competing will be Buena Park's Heather Garritson, who already has 
set the freshman record at the Laguna Hills Invitational and won the Division 
III frosh-soph race at the Woodbridge Invitational. MATT FARMER 
</P>
