<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; WOODBRIDGE KNOCKS OFF CORONA DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Woodbridge won a tie-breaker to upset No. 9 Corona del Mar in Sea View League 
boys' cross-country. 
</P>
<P>
 The Warriors' Jon Jeffrey had the fastest sixth-place finish (17 minutes 3 
seconds), giving Woodbridge the victory at home Thursday after a 28-28 tie. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea Kings' Brian Slingsby finished first on the three-mile course in 
15:29, but the Warriors' Ross Venook (15:37) and Sherman Steve (15:46) took 
second and third to lead Woodbridge (1-0) over last year's league co-champions. 
Corona del Mar is 0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Century League: 
</P>
<P>
 Orange 25, Villa Park 31 -- The 10th-ranked Panthers upset No. 5 Villa Park. 
Glenn Busch finished first in 15:48 for Orange (2-0) at Irvine Park's 3.1-mile 
course. Jeremy Mordock of Villa Park finished second in 15:58 and Joaquin 
Aceves was third in 15:49. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Empire League: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 19, Century 38 -- Top-ranked Katella (1-0) won its league opener as 
Edgar Benitez, Erick Miramontes and Juan Venegas finished within three seconds 
of each other. Miramontes won in 15:44, Miramontes was second in 15:45 and 
Venegas finished in 15:47. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Golden West League: 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 15, Westminster 50; Santa Ana 15, Westminster 50; Santa Ana 24, Tustin 
31 -- Santa Ana's Luis Zaragoza was first on the Tustin course, finishing in 
15:44. Teammate Danny Rivero, 0.10 seconds behind Zaragoza, was second. 
Fourth-ranked Santa Ana is 2-0, Tustin 1-1 and Westminster 0-2. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Golden West League: 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 21, Westminster 35; Tustin 24, Santa Ana 31; Santa Ana 23, Westminster 
32 -- Mandy Reigle finished first for Tustin in 19:13. Tustin is 2-0, Santa Ana 
1-1 and Westminster 0-2. 
