<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: EL RIO; YOUTH, 17, ARRESTED IN ROBBERY, CAR THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 17-year-old El Rio boy was arrested Thursday for allegedly robbing a man at 
gunpoint, stealing his car and stripping parts from the vehicle, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The incident began about 11:15 a.m. when the youth approached Jesus Ahumada, 
22, of Nyeland Acres and asked him for a ride.Once in the car with Ahumada, 
with whom the youth was previously acquainted, the suspect jammed a gun against 
Ahumada's ribs and ordered him to drive to Simi Valley, Ventura County 
sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspect then changed his mind, took $33 from Ahumada and ordered him out 
of the car. Ahumada returned to his home and called for help. 
</P>
<P>
 When deputies went to the youth's home in El Rio, the boy ran to a nearby 
home, where he was found hiding in a closet. He was arrested after deputies 
subdued him with pepper spray. 
</P>
<P>
 Ahumada's car was found later in Nyeland Acres. It had been stripped of its 
stereo, amplifier, speakers and wheels.  
</P>
<P>
 Through the investigation, deputies also identified and arrested a second 
suspect for his alleged role in the thefts. Fernando Candido, 18, of El Rio was 
arrested and booked into Ventura County Jail on suspicion of possessing stolen 
property. JULIE FIELDS 
