<TEXT>
<P>
 To keep children from being exposed to sexually explicit magazines at 
convenience stores, the Camarillo Planning Commission has proposed amending 
city codes to force shopkeepers to cover magazine racks holding the 
publications. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission approved the so-called blinder code on a 4-0 vote Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 "We think is an appropriate action to take," Planning Commission Chairman Les 
Meredith said. "(The code) is a solution to a serious concern in the 
community." 
</P>
<P>
 The change, which still must be adopted by the City Council, would not affect 
adult businesses in the city, officials said. J.E. MITCHELL 
