By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Newbury Park man pleaded guilty Thursday in the attempted rapes of two 
elderly Thousand Oaks women in May. 
</P>
<P>
 David Paul Stewart will face 8 1/4 years in prison at his scheduled Oct. 28 
sentencing, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
 Stewart, 33, entered guilty pleas in Ventura County Superior Court to two 
counts of assault with the intent to commit rape. He had entered a plea of not 
guilty by reason of insanity on Sept. 1. The victims are 87 and 73. 
</P>
<P>
 At a June 30 preliminary hearing, the older victim said she fought Stewart off 
