<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL ROUNDUP; HAWKINS' TWO TOUCHDOWNS PACE NORDHOFF'S 18-7 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nordhoff High's backfield duo of Josh Hawkins and Dallan Rigby combined for 
125 yards in an 18-7 nonleague victory Thursday night over St. Bonaventure at 
Ventura High. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawkins rushed for 79 yards in 16 carries and scored on runs of one and eight 
yards. Rigby rushed for 59 yards in 12 carries and had a one-yard touchdown run 
in the first quarter, bringing Nordhoff (3-0) within a point of St. 
Bonaventure. 
</P>
<P>
 Topi Sanchez gained 79 yards in 25 carries, and Steve Ruelas had 96 yards in 
16 carries for St. Bonaventure, but the Seraphs only scored on their opening 
drive -- Sanchez's one-yard run capping a 69-yard advance. BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
