<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRAWLEY WRAPS UP TENNIS TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Newbury Park High and Villanova Prep standout Sean Brawley captured the 
men's open singles division of the $30,000 United States Professional Tennis 
Assn.National Tournament at La Quinta Resort & Club in La Quinta. 
</P>
<P>
 Fifth-seeded Brawley defeated No. 3 R.J. Dunkle of Duluth, Ga., 4-6, 7-6, 6-1. 
Brawley, 33, played at USC before turning professional. He recently became 
director of tennis at Spanish Hills Country Club in Camarillo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
