<HEADLINE>
<P>
RUPTURED WATER LINE FORCES GAME RELOCATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE TERRY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A water line ruptured Thursday under the Huntington Beach High School football 
field, leaving the field unplayable, and forcing the relocation of tonight's 
game between Ocean View and Century. 
</P>
<P>
 Maintenance manager John Klungreseter said a "bubble of water" formed under 
the dirt, eventually creating a large, mushy hole at the 50-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's rare for the plastic pipes to give way like that; it's the first time in 
at least two years," Klungreseter said. The Ocean View-Century game has been 
relocated to Westminster High; kickoff is 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Principal John Staunton said there did not appear to be any vandalism 
involved. MIKE TERRY 
</P>
</TEXT>
