FEWER THAN 100 TICKETS LEFT FOR CHAPMAN GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fewer than 100 tickets remain for Chapman's football home opener Saturday, the 
athletic department announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman, which playing its first football season since 1932, will play 
Claremont-Mudd at 7 p.m. in the Panthers' on-campus stadium. The stadium holds 
about 2,500 spectators. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets can be purchased at the athletic department office starting at 8 this 
morning. 
</P>
<P>
 No tickets will be sold at the gate Saturday. 
</P>
