<P>
BRIEFLY: TECHNOLOGY & TELECOMMUNICATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Six Baby Bells Form Alliance: In what may reflect a trend toward greater 
cooperation among the offspring of AT&T, six regional Bell telephone companies 
-- including Pacific Bell -- announced an arrangement to jointly market certain 
communications services. Called Unibridge, the service is targeted at companies 
that acquire personal communications systems (PCS) licenses in the upcoming 
Federal Communications Commission auction.Those companies may want to offer 
cellular phone-type PCS services but may not want immediately to invest huge 
sums in the communications infrastructure required to do so. The service would 
offer information about a set of compatible products provided by all the phone 
companies, such as billing, transport and connection to the public switched 
network. The members -- Ameritech, Bell Atlantic, BellSouth, Nynex, Pacific 
Bell and US West -- will cover 43 states. 
</P>
