EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; MTV'S MCGRATH DRAWS UP A NEW PLAYERS LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A long-rumored shake-up at MTV has finally happened, with Judy McGrath, 
recently appointed sole president of the music channel, naming a new executive 
team and reorganizing the music departments. 
</P>
<P>
 Rich Eigendorff was named executive vice president, business operations, and 
Doug Herzog was named executive vice president, production and programming. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, John Cannelli was named to the new job of senior vice president, 
music program development. Andy Schuon will work as senior vice president, 
music and programming, and Van Toffler will be senior vice president, program 
enterprises and business development. McGrath also named Abby Terkuhle senior 
vice president, creative director. 
</P>
<P>
 * Viacom's Fred Schneier was elected to a two-year term as vice chairman of 
the American Film Marketing Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bruce J. Sallan is the new executive producer for drama and specials at New 
World Entertainment. Karen Danaher-Dorr was named senior vice president of 
motion pictures and miniseries. 
</P>
<P>
 * Caroline Andoscia has joined Lawrence Gordon Productions as a supervisor of 
creative development. 
</P>
<P>
 * Castle Rock Entertainment named Melissa Hufjay and Shannon Clark as 
publicists, and David Blasucci was promoted to senior administrator of 
publicity services. 
</P>
<P>
 * Barry Staff has been appointed vice president, publicity for Saban 
Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Miramax Films named Janet Hill to vice president, West Coast publicity, and 
Teri Kane to vice president, publicity in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jeffrey M. Freedman joined the law firm of Sinclair Tenenbaum Olesiuk in the 
motion picture and television area. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ricki L. Seidman is the new executive director of the music industry's Rock 
the Vote organization. 
</P>
<P>
 * Atlantic Records named rock producer Dave Jerden as a vice president. 
</P>
