<P>
PRENATAL PLAN GIVES TOKOS A 23% BOOST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The stock of Tokos Medical Corp. jumped $1.375 Thursday to close at $7.25 in 
trading on the NASDAQ market. 
</P>
<P>
 The 23% price increase was triggered by news that a unit of Fountain 
Valley-based FHP Healthcare cut costs in its neonatal intensive care operation 
by 34% after implementing a maternity risk management program designed by 
Tokos. 
</P>
<P>
 The Santa Ana company's program, used by FHP's Comprecare subsidiary in 
Colorado, provides prenatal education, risk screening and preventive measures 
for women with high-risk pregnancies. 
</P>
