POLICE FOIL BREAK-IN AT STORAGE FACILITY; 3 MEN ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Huntington Beach men were arrested and $10,000 in stolen goods recovered 
after authorities foiled a break-in at a Fountain Valley storage facility, 
police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said the goods -- stereo equipment, videocassette recorders, 
tools, cameras and cellular telephones -- were stolen during break-ins in 
Fountain Valley and Huntington Beach since last December. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley Police Sgt. Dann Bean said police on Monday caught two men 
breaking into lockers at a Newhope Street storage facility and putting the 
stolen items into their own rented locker there. Bean said the men were cutting 
the locks on the storage lockers. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Scott Anderson, 21, and Martin Calloway, 19, at the facility, 
Bean said. The pair shared their rented locker with Matthew Maynard, 22, who 
was arrested later at his home, where police found other stolen property, Bean 
said.  
</P>
<P>
 All three have been booked into Orange County Jail on suspicion of burglary 
and held on $25,000 bail, Bean said. 
