<P>
TUSTIN MAN DIES OF BAR FIGHT WOUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 40-year-old Tustin man died Thursday of injuries sustained in a Sept. 2 bar 
fight in Santa Ana, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Eucario Osorio, who died at Chapman General Hospital in Orange, was 
kicked in the head during the fight at Broadway Billiards Parlor, in the 200 
block of North Broadway, by a man who is still at large, Lt. Robert Helton 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Osorio did not regain consciousness long enough to be interviewed by police, 
Helton said. 
</P>
<P>
