<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN REACHES SPONSORSHIP AGREEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pepsi-Cola and Cal State Northridge have reached a working agreement that will 
be worth $500,000 to the Matador athletic program over the next 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
 The agreement will make Pepsi the official soft drink of Northridge's athletic 
program and award $50,000 a year for the next 10 years to the school's sports 
program. 
</P>
<P>
 The bulk of the funds will be used to replace the scoreboards at Northridge's 
football-soccer, baseball and softball facilities. 
</P>
<P>
 The Matadors' football-soccer scoreboard is 23 years old and the scoreboards 
for baseball and softball have been in use for more than 10 years. Pepsi-Cola 
will receive major signage on all Northridge scoreboards. 
</P>
<P>
 "This sponsorship will allow us to begin improving our athletic facilities to 
the standards expected at the NCAA Division I level," Northridge Athletic 
Director Bob Hiegert said. 
</P>
<P>
 The sponsorship went into effect Sept. 14. 
</P>
