<HEADLINE>
<P>
OC HIGH STUDENTS NEWS AND VIEWS; INLINE; MAKING A DIFFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Looking for a way to work with others to make things better at your school or 
in your community? Make a Difference Day, a national day of community service, 
is being celebrated in Orange County on Oct. 22 and offers opportunities to do 
just that. 
</P>
<P>
 The event encourages projects by individual students, service clubs or entire 
schools. For information, call the Make a Difference Day hot line at (714) 
647-2600. Call the same number to request the Volunteer Center of Orange 
County's booklet, "101 Ways to Make a Difference." 
</P>
<P>
 Tricia Michels, junior  
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley High School  
</P>
