<HEADLINE>
<P>
OC HIGH STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS; INLINE; DEDICATING SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To mark the completion of Aliso Niguel High School, a community festival, 
concert and dedication ceremony will be held Saturday at the school, 28000 
Terrace View Drive, Aliso Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 Dedication is slated for 1 p.m.; school tours will begin at 2 p.m. There will 
be food, game and information booths and performances by the school's marching 
band, dance team, pep squad and choral group throughout the day. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will conclude with a 6 p.m. concert by the Drifters and the Coasters 
at the school's Wolverine Stadium. Concert tickets are $3 for adults, $1 for 
children and are available at the gate. 
</P>
