<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Expect even more shops to pop up around South Coast Plaza in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 The Arnel Development Co. recently received approval to build a 
400,000-square-foot shopping center complete with a 10-screen movie complex and 
food court across South Coast Drive from Crystal Court at Bear Street. 
</P>
<P>
 The South Coast Boardwalk will also feature electronics, book and clothing 
retailers. 
</P>
<P>
 The shopping center is expected to be completed in November, 1995. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Residents from around Orange County will examine ways of improving the 
American political system at a forum in San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting, sponsored by the National Issues Forum of Orange County, is one 
of nine being held over the next few weeks. The aim of the forum is to find 
ways of increasing participation in government and promoting "personal 
responsibility." The forum will also look at the role of special interest 
groups in government. 
</P>
<P>
 The discussion will run from 2 to 4 p.m. at the San Diego Gas & Electric 
office in San Clemente. For more information, call (714) 724-1412. 
</P>
